Mohammed Ovajimo, the photographer to First Lady, Aisha Buhari, has passed away. He died on Wednesday after a brief illness in Abuja, the nation’s capital. Born May 12, 1982, Ovajimo hailed from Kogi State. Director Information in the Office of the First lady, Suleiman Haruna, confirmed his demise. “Today, we lost Mohammed Yusuf Ovajimo, a professional photographer of the First Lady of Nigeria”, he wrote on Facebook. Haruna described the deceased as an accomplished professional with loads of skill and great human relations. The spokesman said Ovajimo will be greatly missed and prayed his soul rests in peace.